data.chText: 速度；进度
data.enText: a measurement of the speed at which sth happens

data.chText: 大多数人步行的平均速度为每小时5公里。
data.enText: Most people walk at an average rate of 5 kilometres an hour.

data.chText: 报警案件的数量正在以惊人的速度增长。
data.enText: The number of reported crimes is increasing at an alarming rate.

data.chText: 今天公布的数字表明通货膨胀率又一次下降。
data.enText: Figures published today show another fall in the rate of inflation.

data.chText: 以你工作的速度，你永远也做不完！
data.enText: At the rate you work, you'll never finish!

data.chText: 比率；率
data.enText: a measurement of the number of times sth happens or exists during a particular period

data.chText: 地方企业正在以每年三家的速度关闭。
data.enText: Local businesses are closing at a/the rate of three a year.

data.chText: 高 / 低 / 不断增长的失业率
data.enText: a high/low/rising rate of unemployment

data.chText: 年犯罪 / 离婚率
data.enText: the annual crime/divorce rate

data.chText: 他的脉搏速率突然下降。
data.enText: His pulse rate dropped suddenly.

data.chText: 很高的成功 / 失败率
data.enText: a high success/failure rate

data.chText: 价格；费用
data.enText: a fixed amount of money that is charged or paid for sth

data.chText: 广告费、保险费、邮费等
data.enText: advertising/insurance/postal, etc. rates

data.chText: 按小时支付的低 / 高报酬
data.enText: a low/high hourly rate of pay

data.chText: 我们对学生有特惠价格。
data.enText: We offer special reduced rates for students.

data.chText: 定额偿还按揭贷款
data.enText: a fixed-rate mortgage (= one in which the amount of money paid back each month is fixed for a particular period)

data.chText: 基本税额
data.enText: the basic rate of tax (= the lowest amount that is paid by everyone)

data.chText: 汇率；利率
data.enText: exchange/interest rates

data.chText: 汇率；利率
data.enText: rates of exchange/interest

data.chText: （英国地方政府征收的）房地产税，房产税
data.enText: (in Britain) a tax paid by businesses to a local authority for land and buildings that they use and in the past also paid by anyone who owned a house
at any rate

data.chText: （强调事情的真实性）无论如何，不管怎样
data.enText: used to say that a particular fact is true despite what has happened in the past or what may happen in the future

data.chText: 不管怎么说，这是个好消息。
data.enText: Well, that's one good piece of news at any rate.

data.chText: 我下周可能要出差，但无论如何，我最晚星期五回来。
data.enText: I may be away on business next week but at any rate I'll be back by Friday.

data.chText: （表示说得更加确切）不管怎样，至少
data.enText: used to show that you are being more accurate about sth that you have just said

data.chText: 他说他明天要来。至少，我认为他是这么说的。
data.enText: He said he'll be coming tomorrow. At any rate, I think that's what he said.

data.chText: （强调下文）总而言之，反正
data.enText: used to show that what you have just said is not as important as what you are going to say

data.chText: 那里也许有六七十人吧。反正屋子里挤得严严实实。
data.enText: There were maybe 60 or 70 people there. At any rate, the room was packed.
at a rate of knots

data.chText: 飞快地；迅速地
data.enText: very quickly
at this/that rate

data.chText: 照此情形；如此下去
data.enText: used to say what will happen if a particular situation continues to develop in the same way

data.chText: 照此情形，我们很快就会破产。
data.enText: At this rate, we'll soon be bankrupt.

data.chText: 不用于进行时
data.enText: not used in the progressive tenses

data.chText: 评估；评价；估价
data.enText: to have or think that sb/sth has a particular level of quality, value, etc.

data.chText: 这所大学因其研究工作而受到高度评价。
data.enText: The university is highly rated for its research.

data.chText: 作为同事，他们对他评价甚高。
data.enText: They rated him highly as a colleague.

data.chText: 选民继续把教育看作是头等重要的大事。
data.enText: Voters continue to rate education high on their list of priorities.

data.chText: 评论家和观众都认为这次演出是成功的。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+名词短语

data.enText: The show was rated (as) a success by critics and audiences.

data.chText: 这次比赛可以说是他们最为惨重的一次失败。
data.enText: The match rated as one of their worst defeats.

data.chText: 我们的需求恐怕不会受到这届政府的多大重视。
data.enText: I'm afraid our needs do not rate very high with this administration.

data.chText: 认为…是好的；看好
data.enText: to think that sb/sth is good

data.chText: 你觉得这部电影怎么样？我本人认为不怎么样。
data.enText: What did you think of the movie? I didn't rate it myself.

data.chText: 划分等级；分等
data.enText: to place sb/sth in a particular position on a scale in relation to similar people or things

data.chText: 这些学校是按考试成绩排名次的。
data.enText: The schools were rated according to their exam results.

data.chText: 一级项目
data.enText: a top-rated programme

data.chText: 她目前排名世界第二。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+名词短语

data.enText: She is currently rated number two in the world.

data.chText: 值得，配得上（某种对待）
data.enText: to be good, important, etc. enough to be treated in a particular way

data.chText: 这件事在报纸上连提都不值得一提。
data.enText: The incident didn't even rate a mention in the press.

data.chText: 对（电影或录像片）分级
data.enText: to state that a film/movie or video is suitable for a particular audience

data.text: rate ♦ charge ♦ fee ♦ rent ♦ dues ♦ toll ♦ rental ♦ tariff

data.chText: 以上各词均指所收取或付出的费用。
data.enText: These are all words for an amount of money that is charged or paid for sth.
rate

data.chText: 指所索取或付出的价格、费用：
data.enText: a fixed amount of money that is asked or paid for sth

data.chText: 按小时支付的低报酬
data.enText: a low hourly rate of pay

data.chText: 利率
data.enText: interest rates
charge

data.chText: 指商品或服务的要价、收费：
data.enText: an amount of money that is asked for goods or services

data.chText: 入场费
data.enText: an admission charge
fee

data.chText: 指专业服务费、咨询费、学费、会费：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) an amount of money that you have to pay for professional advice or services, to go to a school or college, or to join an organization

data.chText: 诉讼费
data.enText: legal fees

data.chText: 年度会员费
data.enText: an annual membership fee
rent

data.chText: 指房屋租金。
data.enText: an amount of money that you regularly have to pay for use of a building or room

data.chText: 在美国英语中，rent可用以表示rental（租金）：
data.enText: In American English, rent can be used to mean rental .

data.chText: 这辆汽车每周的租金是200多元。
data.enText: The weekly rent on the car was over $200.
dues

data.chText: 指应缴会员费
data.enText: an amount of money that you have to pay so that you can be a member of an organization
toll

data.chText: 指道路、桥梁的通行费
data.enText: an amount of money that you have to pay to use a particular road or bridge
rental

data.chText: 指租金
data.enText: an amount of money that you have to pay to use sth for a particular period of time

data.chText: 用rent还是rental？
在英国英语中，rent只指房屋租金，其他物品的租金用rental。在美国英语中，rent可指以上两种租金，但指其他物品的租金，rental仍然较通用。
data.enText: In British English rent is only money paid to use a building or room: for other items use rental . In American English rent can be used for both, but rental is still more common for other items.
rent or rental?
tariff

data.chText: 指旅馆、餐馆或公司的服务价目表、收费表
data.enText: ( rather formal ) a list of fixed prices that are charged by a hotel or restaurant for rooms or meals, or by a company for a particular service
to pay (a) rate/charge/fee/rent/dues/toll/rental for/on sth
to do sth at a rate/charge/fee/rent/rental of…
to do sth for a charge/fee
to pay (a) rate/charge/fee/rent/dues/toll/rental
to charge (a) rate/fee/rent/dues/toll/rental

ex.enText: The train went by at high speed.

ex.chText: 这架新飞机的时速可以达到900公里。
ex.enText: This new plane can reach a speed of 900 kilometres an hour.

ex.chText: 我们必须加快送货速度。
ex.enText: We had to increase the speed of delivery.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，指交通工具等运动的速率或事情发生的速度。

ex.enText: The pace of change has accelerated.

ex.chText: 在当今世界，人类进步一日千里。
ex.enText: In the world today, mankind is progressing at a tremendous pace.

synonyms.bx: 指人步行的速度，常引申为生活、变化等的速度。

ex.chText: 他的钱用得很快，速度惊人。
ex.enText: His money was running out at an alarming rate/speed.
The rate/speed of economic growth has slowed down.

synonyms.bx: 常指某事在一段时间内发生的速度，可与 speed 换用。

ex.chText: 喷气机正在以音速飞行。
ex.enText: The jet plane is flying at the velocity of sound.

ex.chText: 要求学生计算出光的速度。
ex.enText: The students were asked to calculate the velocity of light.
Leopards can move with an astonishing velocity.

synonyms.bx: 物理学术语，指物体沿着一定方向运动时的速度；作普通意义上的速度解时，则指高速。

ex.zh: 高速；高费率；高税率；高利率
低速；低费率；低税率；低利率

data.chText: 他们支付的酬金略高于现行标准。

tr: the relative speed of progress or change
example: he lived at a fast pace
he works at a great rate

tr: amount of a charge or payment relative to some basis
example: a 10-minute phone call at that rate would cost $5

tr: a quantity or amount or measure considered as a proportion of another quantity or amount or measure
a magnitude or frequency relative to a time unit
example: they traveled at a rate of 55 miles per hour
the rate of change was faster than expected

tr: assign a rank or rating to
example: how would you rank these students?
The restaurant is rated highly in the food guide
How would you rate his chances to become President?
Gold was rated highly among the Romans

tr: be worthy of or have a certain rating

value.def: The rate at which something happens is the speed with which it happens.

example.ex: The rate at which hair grows can be agonisingly slow...
example.tran: 头发生长的速度可能极其缓慢。

example.ex: The world's tropical forests are disappearing at an even faster rate than experts had thought.
example.tran: 世界上热带森林消失的速度比专家们预想的还要快。

value.def: The rate at which something happens is the number of times it happens over a period of time.

example.ex: New diet books appear at a rate of nearly one a week...
example.tran: 新的饮食类书籍差不多一周出一本。

example.ex: His heart rate was 30 beats per minute slower...
example.tran: 他的心率每分钟慢了30次。

example.ex: Britain held the unenviable record of having the highest divorce rate in Europe.
example.tran: 英国在欧洲各国中保持着不光彩的最高离婚率纪录。

value.def: A rate is the amount of money that is charged for goods or services.

example.ex: Calls cost 36p per minute cheap rate and 48p at all other times.
example.tran: 优惠时段的话费是每分钟36便士，其他时段是48便士。

example.ex: ...specially reduced rates for travellers using Gatwick Airport...
example.tran: 为在盖特威克机场进出港的乘客提供的优惠价格

example.ex: East German wages were converted at the rate of one old East mark for one Deutschmark.
example.tran: 东德的工资兑换比率是一个旧东德马克兑换一个德国马克。

value.def: The rate of taxation or interest is the amount of tax or interest that needs to be paid. It is expressed as a percentage of the amount that is earned, gained as profit, or borrowed.

example.ex: The government insisted that it would not be panicked into interest rate cuts.
example.tran: 政府坚称不会陷入恐慌而匆忙降息。

value.def: In Britain, the rates were a local tax which you paid if you owned property or if you rented property without furniture.

example.ex: Soldiers were exempt from paying rates...
example.tran: 士兵免缴地方税。

example.ex: The new council tax combines elements of both the community charge and the rates.
example.tran: 新的家庭税合并了人头税和地方税两个税种。

value.tran: （英国）地方税，不动产税，房地产税

value.def: If you rate someone or something as good or bad, you consider them to be good or bad. You can also say that someone or something rates as good or bad.

example.ex: Of all the men in the survey, they rate themselves the least fun-loving and the most responsible...
example.tran: 在所有参加调查的人中，他们认为自己最不贪玩、最负责任。

example.ex: The film was rated excellent by 90 per cent of children...
example.tran: 90%的孩子都表示这部电影很精彩。

example.ex: Most rated it a hit...
example.tran: 大多数人认为它很受欢迎。

example.ex: We rate him as one of the best...
example.tran: 我们认为他是其中佼佼者之一。

example.ex: She rated the course highly...
example.tran: 她对这门课的评价很高。

example.ex: Reading books does not rate highly among Britons as a leisure activity.
example.tran: 读书并非英国人很喜欢的休闲活动。

example.ex: ...the most highly rated player in English football.
example.tran: 英格兰足球界最受好评的球员

value.def: If you rate someone or something, you think that they are good.

example.ex: It's flattering to know that other clubs have shown interest and seem to rate me...
example.tran: 得知其他俱乐部对我感兴趣并看好我令我受宠若惊。

example.ex: Its artistic value failed to move Paddy Clegg. 'I don't know what all the fuss is about. I didn't rate it at all,' he said.
example.tran: 它的艺术价值没能打动帕迪·克莱格。“我不知道这样大惊小怪是为什么。我一点儿也不看好它，”他说道。

value.def: If someone or something is rated at a particular position or rank, they are calculated or considered to be in that position on a list.

example.ex: He is generally rated Italy's No. 3 industrialist...
example.tran: 他被公认为意大利第三大实业家。

example.ex: He came here rated 100th on the tennis computer.
example.tran: 他以网坛排名第100名的身份来到这里。

value.tran: 把…评为;把…认定为;把…列为

value.def: If you say that someone or something rates a particular reaction, you mean that this is the reaction you consider to be appropriate.

example.ex: This is so extraordinary, it rates a medal and a phone call from the President...
example.tran: 这简直不可思议，应该得到一枚奖章以及总统的电话祝贺。

example.ex: In those crowded streets her attire did not rate a second glance.
example.tran: 在那些拥挤的街道她的穿着并未引起注意。

value.def: You use at any rate to indicate that what you have just said might be incorrect or unclear in some way, and that you are now being more precise.

example.ex: She modestly suggests that 'sex, or at any rate gender, may account for the difference'...
example.tran: 她谨慎地提出“性别，至少是男女的性征，也许能解释这个差异”。

example.ex: He is the least appealing character, to me at any rate.
example.tran: 他是其中最没有吸引力的角色，至少对我来说是这样。

value.def: You use at any rate to indicate that the important thing is what you are saying now, and not what was said before.

example.ex: At any rate, Pankin said that relations between the two nations will be restored before the conference...
example.tran: 不管怎样，潘金说两国之间的关系将在会谈之前恢复。

example.ex: Well, at any rate, let me thank you for all you did.
example.tran: 好吧，不管怎样，还是要感谢你所做的一切。

value.tran: 不管怎样，无论如何（表示现在所说的话更为重要、而非之前所言）

value.def: If you say that at this rate something bad or extreme will happen, you mean that it will happen if things continue to develop as they have been doing.

example.ex: At this rate, she would be almost seven feet tall by then...
example.tran: 这样下去，她到时将有7英尺高了。

example.ex: At this rate they'd be lucky to get home before eight-thirty or nine.
example.tran: 这样看来他们能在8点半或是9点以前到家就算幸运了。

value.tran: 这样下去；长此以往；如此一来
